  "scientific_question": "Third independent topology regime test. PDAC network has a distinct structural assignment from NSCLC and CRC: CDK4 is the largest druggable structural damper (delta_r=+0.295), AKT1 is a moderate damper (+0.131, vs anchor in NSCLC/CRC), PI3K and MEK1 are small dampers (~+0.073-0.075), and mTOR is the only anchor (-0.075). ODS predicts: CDK4/6 inhibitors should outperform mTOR inhibitors in KRAS-dep PDAC. Biological note: CDKN2A is deleted ~90% PDAC, making CDK4 constitutively active -- the structural damper position and the pharmacological vulnerability coincide. AKT1 flipping to damper (from anchor in NSCLC/CRC) tests whether AKT inhibitors are more effective in PDAC than in NSCLC/CRC, consistent with topology.",
