      "id": "h1",
      "statement": "Spearman r(delta_r, mean PRISM LFC) < -0.40 across 5 node-drug class pairs (CDK4, AKT1, PI3K, MEK1, mTOR) within pancreas lines filtered to KRAS Chronos < -0.5. n=5 nodes. delta_r range is larger than prior tests (+0.295 to -0.075). Larger range should improve correlation if ODS holds."
    },
    {
      "id": "h2",
      "label": "Primary topology-regime test (3rd cancer type)",
      "statement": "CDK4 mean PRISM LFC < mTOR mean PRISM LFC within KRAS Chronos < -0.5 pancreas lines. CDK4 is the largest structural damper (delta_r=+0.295); mTOR is the anchor (delta_r=-0.075). Prior confirmations: NSCLC mTOR(damper)>MEK1(anchor) CONFIRMED; CRC MEK1(damper)>mTOR(anchor) CONFIRMED. CDK4/6 inhibitors in PDAC: biologically plausible because CDKN2A deletion (~90% PDAC) makes CDK4 constitutively active -- the structural damper assignment and pharmacological vulnerability coincide."
    },
    {
      "id": "h3",
      "label": "AKT1 topology flip test",
      "statement": "AKT1 mean PRISM LFC in PDAC < AKT1 mean PRISM LFC in NSCLC (from D3_v2: -0.081). AKT1 is a damper in PDAC (delta_r=+0.131) vs anchor in NSCLC (delta_r=-0.024). ODS predicts AKT inhibitors should be more effective in PDAC than in NSCLC. NSCLC reference value: -0.081 (from D3_v2 outputs/D3_v2_KRAS_stratified_results.json). This tests whether individual node topology changes predict drug efficacy changes independent of the cancer-level H2 comparison."
